	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.54]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>These spells have been a constant frustration for me and I'm nearly ready to write them off as useless.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>From what I gather, the lull line basically does the Obi Wan thing "These aren't the droids you're looking for... we can be on our way."  In other words you lower agression to be able to single pull mobs.  <br><br>Never works though.  Half the time the thing still agros, and the other half the time it resists and agros, bringing the whole place down on your head.  <br><br>Am I doing something wrong?  Is there a specific use for this spell or a better way to use it?  How does it stack up against the harmony line of spells?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
