<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100664048930919></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100664048930919><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100664048930919>The Guild Question</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100664048930919#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83710><span id=Scholar>jcasetnl</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>147 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Nov 24th 5:21 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi all, I'm looking for general feedback from those of you who are in guilds about your experiences.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm mainly looking for information from a playing experience aspect, not from a "you'll make lifelong friends and meet great people" aspect.  <br><br>If it were my choice, I wouldn't even join a guild.  I have nothing against them but it's not really my style.  But unfortunately, something I began to realize around lvl 20 is coming to fruition: it is becoming more and more difficult to solo or find pickup groups.  Yes, it *can* be done, I realize, but it has become increasingly more frustrating.<br><br>Further, I'm tired of put together groups that, let's face it, suck.  They get you in the door, sure, but forget about crawling in most cases.  Either people leave at the worst times or they simply can't play their characters well.<br><br>Okay, enough ranting.  So, my question is, has joining a guild helped to better your game by providing more serious and consistent partners?  What kind of problems have been introduced in your game by joining a guild?  Have you ever left a guild and why?  Thanks for your assistance!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10068170141668></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10068170141668><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=10068170141668>RE: The Guild Question</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=10068170141668#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=38412><span id=Scholar>Dalantia</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>233 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 26th 6:23 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.09]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Being in the KoB has, bluntly, basically made three differences to my playing life.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am generally favored for groups when there're guildies in the area, very nice equipment is very available for cheaper prices, and raids are easier to find, plan, and carry out.  For example, I'm leading three raids this month for Soulfire hilts and teef, as big sis puts it.  But, other than that, I still generally just wander around and look for pickup groups.<br><br>Quote:<br>So, my question is, has joining a guild helped to better your game by providing more serious and consistent partners?<br><br>To an extent.  Serious and consistent partners more often find their way into my friends list than when I do /who all kings.  However, with a few notable exceptions, all the KoBers I group and raid with have been much more interested in the battle and play their classes well, rather than socialize.<br><br>Quote:<br>What kind of problems have been introduced in your game by joining a guild?<br><br>None.  The KoB has a good reputation and is one of the larger guilds on Fennin Ro.  But, remember, when you wear the tag, what everyone else does reflects on you and what you do reflects on everyone else.  But, generally, other than the addition of what the guild expects (not difficult, for me at least) and obligations, it has not made too many problems for me.<br><br>Quote:<br>Have you ever left a guild and why?<br><br>I was originally in Takara Kei, led by my character's big sis (Yes, he married her cousin, no, they're not blood relations).  The guild disbanded and the vast majority of them left for the Second Foundation, while I had promised Souldragoon that I would join the KoB if Takara didn't work out.  I left the KoB for the Second Foundation for a while, to see what it was like.  While, individually, I regard the vast majority of them as friends, I did not mesh with them as a whole, and left to rejoin the Kings.<br><br>If the Kings were to split up, I would likely remain guildless.<br><br>I would like to let you know, however, that some guilds, if you build up a good rep with their leaders and members, will let you raid and group with them as an equal member.  Second Foundation does, for example.<br>&nbsp;<br>Dalantia Dragonet<br>Aiyeka's Beloved Guardian, 41st Rank<br>Fennin Ro<br>Kings of Brotherhood</td></tr>
