	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Dinerian,<br><br>Unless you have another haste item like an FBSS, Sash of the Dragonborne or Swirlspine belt (just to name a few) the Mithril 2-hand Sword is about at the top of the list, short of weapons such as found in ToV or Sleeper's Tomb.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, if you do have another haste item, then there are several weapons that will outdamage a mithril 2-hand sword, but don't just assume so.  Do some research. For example, a mithril 2-hand sword will outdamage an FBSS/Wurmslayer combination.<br><br>With another haste item, the Arbitor's Combine Greatsword is an awesome choice. I was not aware of the upgrade to this sword mentioned in the post by Balidin and I recently sold one, so it must be VERY recent.  But even without the upgrade, the ACG, combined with haste, is a GREAT combination. No doubt about it.  Many of the 30/40 weapons that drop in Dragon Necropolis are also very nice when combined with haste...but ONLY if combined with another haste item.<br><br>Without haste...keep your Mithral 2-hander. It's hard to beat.<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
