	   <tr><td colspan=2>Soulfire IMHO is not really that important to a paladin until he is almost epic status.&nbsp;&nbsp;I made the mistake of finishing this quest at 34 and making myself KOS to east and west freeport (which is btw too late for me to switch since i've killed Sir Lucan almost 7 different times since then).  My advice is to do this quest once you are ready to do the FA quest.  <br>In any case a better sword than a Mithril two hander is probably an Arbitors Combine Greatsword...really good sword for paladins until you get epic status or be lucky enough to be in an uber guild that can get you a Primal/Priceless Velium Warsword from Sleeper's Tomb.  <br>Arbitors Combine Greatsword is 33/40 +15wis and some hp/mana increase, dmg bonus 7(i think, but then again I could be wrong)  This sword kicks butt with an FBSS or any type of haste item and depending on your server it can cost you from around 2-3kPP.  Another good sword is an Argent Defender 33/49...Argent Protector 40/49(aarrghh..lost the roll for this sword=P)...light/heavy velium claidmore or warlance...the prices for all these varies per server and I suggest waiting on SoL to come out before buying any since there might be an even better super weapon for paladins=)  Until then...Good luck on your quest for soulfire!!!<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Dwarven pally</td></tr>
